%[text] # MATLAB Mobile Receiver
%[text] Receive sensor data and camera images from MATLAB® Mobile™ directly into Simulink®.
%[text] ## Overview
%[text] The **MATLAB Mobile Receiver** block lets you stream live data from a mobile device running MATLAB Mobile into your Simulink model. This includes:
%[text] - Built-in sensors:
%[text]     - Acceleration
%[text]     - Orientation
%[text]     - Angular Velocity
%[text]     - Magnetic Field
%[text]     - GPS
%[text] - Camera images (RGB frames) \
%[text] This enables rapid prototyping, algorithm testing, and interactive simulations using real-world mobile data.
%[text] ## Getting Started
%[text] 1. Install [**MATLAB Mobile**](https://www.mathworks.com/products/matlab-mobile.html) on your mobile device.
%[text] 2. Install **MATLAB Support Package for Android Sensors** or **MATLAB Support Package for Apple iOS Sensors** from the Add-On Explorer \
%[text] On the device, inside MATLAB Mobile:
%[text] 1. Go to **Sensors \> Stream to** and select **MATLAB**.
%[text] 2. Enable
%[text]     - **Sensor Access** -\> Sensors \> More \> Sensor Access
%[text]     - **Camera Access**
%[text] 3. (Optional) On Android, enable **Background Data Acquisition** to allow streaming while the app runs in the background. \
%[text] ## Using the Block
%[text] ![](text:image:43c4)
%[text] 1. Open `MATLABMobileReceiver.prj` in MATLAB.
%[text] 2. Open `MATLABMobileReceiverExample.slx`.
%[text] 3. Run the Simulink model. \
%[text] In the block dialog, enable the outputs you want to stream:
%[text] - **Acceleration** outputs device acceleration as `[X Y Z]`.
%[text] - **Orientation** outputs device orientation as `[Azimuth Pitch Roll]`.
%[text] - **Angular Velocity** outputs angular velocity as `[X Y Z]`.
%[text] - **Position** outputs GPS position as `[Latitude Longitude Altitude]`.
%[text] - **Magnetic Field** outputs magnetic field as `[X Y Z]`.
%[text] - **Camera** outputs RGB camera frames from the selected front or back camera. \
%[text] Set **Frequency** to control the sensor sample rate in Hz. Set **FPS** to control the camera frame rate, or set **FPS** to `0` to expose an external `Shoot` input that captures a frame when triggered.
%[text] ## MathWorks® Products
%[text] Requires MATLAB release **R2026a** or newer and:
%[text] - [MATLAB Mobile](https://www.mathworks.com/products/matlab-mobile.html)
%[text] - [Simulink](https://www.mathworks.com/products/simulink.html)
%[text] - [MATLAB Support Package for Android Sensors](https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/47618-matlab-support-package-for-android-sensors) or [MATLAB Support Package for Apple iOS Sensors](https://www.mathworks.com/matlabcentral/fileexchange/51235-matlab-support-package-for-apple-ios-sensors) \

